UPDATE experiences SET user_reviews = '[{"name":"Michael R.","country":"🇺🇸 United States","rating":5,"date":"2026-01-24","text":"10 tastings in 3 hours — we were absolutely stuffed by the end! The bacalhau and the local cheese were standouts. Highly recommend going hungry.","source":"getyourguide","verified":true},{"name":"Jennifer K.","country":"🇺🇸 United States","rating":4,"date":"2026-01-08","text":"Good experience overall. A few minor things could be improved but nothing significant. We had a great time. Worth it!","source":"viator","verified":true},{"name":"Helena R.","country":"🇵🇱 Poland","rating":5,"date":"2025-12-22","text":"Absolutely fantastic. We discovered flavors we didn''t know existed. The pastéis de bacalhau fresh from the fryer were incredible!","source":"viator","verified":true},{"name":"James T.","country":"🇬🇧 United Kingdom","rating":5,"date":"2025-11-21","text":"As a foodie, this was the highlight of our Lisbon trip. The market stop alone was worth the price. Learned so much about Portuguese flavors.","source":"getyourguide","verified":true},{"name":"Rafael O.","country":"🇧🇷 Brazil","rating":5,"date":"2025-09-30","text":"Such an authentic experience. Small group, no tourist traps. Our guide took us to a local tasca where we were the only foreigners. Pure gold.","source":"viator","verified":true},{"name":"Ana M.","country":"🇪🇸 Spain","rating":4,"date":"2025-08-30","text":"A lovely experience overall. Would have liked a bit more variety in the tastings, but the quality was top-notch and the guide was wonderful.","source":"viator","verified":true},{"name":"Lisa B.","country":"🇩🇪 Germany","rating":5,"date":"2025-07-28","text":"Exceeded all expectations. The guide''s knowledge of food history was impressive. The ginjinha tasting at that tiny bar was an unforgettable moment.","source":"getyourguide","verified":true},{"name":"Martin P.","country":"🇨🇿 Czech Republic","rating":4,"date":"2025-07-13","text":"Good food tour but I''ve done better in other ci